6jnR<?php exit; ?>a:6:{s:10:"last_error";s:0:"";s:10:"last_query";s:129:"SELECT pchc_posts.* FROM pchc_posts WHERE ID IN (502,505,520,522,525,528,531,534,537,540,543,546,549,551,556,559,554,564,561,567)";s:11:"last_result";a:20:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"502";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-08-06 10:38:45";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-08-06 14:38:45";s:12:"post_content";s:1440:"(PCHC) is pleased to host a health and career fair for veterans on Tuesday, August 13th 9am-12pm. Area schools and businesses will be available to help connect attendees to educational and employment opportunities, as well as health care options, and new services for Veterans such as My HealtheVet. Please join us for this exciting, free event honoring those who have served! Stop by and enter to win a door prize. The opening ceremony with keynote speaker Congressman Michael H. Michaud will begin at 9am. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.pchc.com/servingvets">www.pchc.com/servingvets</a>.
<h2>Event Information</h2>
<strong>What:</strong> Serving Those Who Served Event
<strong>Date:</strong> August 13, 2013
<strong>Time:</strong> 9am
<strong>Location:</strong> Eastern Maine Community College, Rangeley Hall, 354 Hogan Road
<strong>Attending:</strong> Area Veterans, Congressman Michael H. Michaud, Kenneth Schmidt, PCHC President &amp; CEO, Dick Bohrer, PCA and Network Relations Director, National Association of Community Health Centers, Penelope Markle, Associate Director VHA Office of Rural Health, and Dan Belyea, Director of Eastern Maine Community College.

The event is made possible by PCHC and the following event sponsors: Maine Primary Care Association, National Association of Community Health Centers, the Veteran’s Administration, Congressman Michael H. Michaud, and Eastern Maine Community College.";s:10:"post_title";s:72:"PCHC Hosting Health & Career Fair for Veterans: Serving Those Who Served";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:69:"pchc-hosting-health-career-fair-for-veterans-serving-those-who-served";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 10:41:11";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 14:41:11";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=502";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"505";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-08-02 10:41:43";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-08-02 14:41:43";s:12:"post_content";s:2150:"On July 15th, Seaport Family Practice in Belfast joined Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) in Bangor and the practice become Seaport Community Health Center.

Seaport Family Practice has been serving Waldo County for almost 30 years. It’s been a state and national leader in the transformation of health care. It has had mental health services integrated into its medical care for 20 years and has used electronic medical records for 12 years. It is a high quality practice, having earned the highest level of national NCQA Patient Centered Medical Home recognition – just like six other PCHC practices. SCHC has six physicians, a physician assistant and a pediatric nurse practitioner, and two licensed clinical social workers. There are about 22 employees in all and together they care for 7,000 patients. The practice provides primary medical care, integrated behavioral health and addiction services, Integrative Medicine, prenatal care &amp; deliveries; it also provides expanded weekend and evening hours, and group visits.

Seaport and PCHC have been working closely together for over three years to plan this development. Both share the same mission and vision – that everyone should have access to the high quality health care services they need regardless of their personal circumstances; and that the health care system needs to be transformed, through a robust Patient Centered Medical Home model, with a wide range of integrated primary care services.

PCHC and SCHC leaders are now focused on development of a new facility for Seaport’s providers and staff and expanding critically needed services for the people of Waldo County. David Loxterkamp, MD, Medical Director of SCHC said, “SCHC will continue to work with Waldo County General Hospital, other community organizations, and its patients, to offer the best possible medical care and attend to the non-medical determinants of health that make us a stronger and happier Waldo County.”

Ken Schmidt, President &amp; CEO of PCHC said, “We are deeply proud and honored to have the dedicated and caring providers and staff of Seaport as colleagues in PCHC.”";s:10:"post_title";s:45:"Seaport Family Practice of Belfast Joins PCHC";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:45:"seaport-family-practice-of-belfast-joins-pchc";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 10:43:03";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 14:43:03";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=505";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"520";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-30 13:47:24";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-30 17:47:24";s:12:"post_content";s:651:"PCHC has partnered with Electronics End, LLC, to offer the public a safe way to dispose of electronic waste. Join us between 10am-2pm on August 3rd at 1012 Union Street, Bangor (beside Burger King) to dispose of old computers, printers, monitors, phones, televisions, gaming consoles, and microwaves. Items with refrigerants, such as air conditioners and refrigerators, will not be accepted.

The event is free and open to the public. Every 25th vehicle will win a prize. Should you have any questions regarding the event or the items that will be accepted, please contact John Ward, Manager of Facilities Logistics, at 207-992-9200 extensions 1374.";s:10:"post_title";s:53:"PCHC to Host Public e-Waste Disposal Event August 3rd";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:53:"pchc-to-host-public-e-waste-disposal-event-august-3rd";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 13:48:10";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 17:48:10";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=520";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"522";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-23 13:48:23";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-23 17:48:23";s:12:"post_content";s:1358:"Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is pleased to announce that Christopher Johnston, DO, has joined the medical staff at PCHC’s Helen Hunt Health Center, 242 Brunswick Street, Old Town. Dr. Johnston’s practice centers on all aspects of high-quality medical care, including patient physicals, acute visits, and health care maintenance.

Dr. Johnston received his undergraduate degree from the University of Maine, his Master’s degree from Clayton College, and his Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine from the University of New England. Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Dr. Johnston also completed a residency program with Maine-Dartmouth Family Medicine Residency and has special interests in Pediatrics, Hospice Care, and Integrative and Complimentary Medicine. Robert Allen, MD, PCHC’s Executive Medical Director, states, “Dr. Johnston is an outstanding physician who is very proactive in patient care and also highly skilled in osteopathic manipulation therapy. Dr. Johnston will be a wonderful new resource for the patients of Old Town.”

Dr. Johnston is accepting new patients at Helen Hunt Health Center; for an appointment please call 207-827-6128. Helen Hunt Health Center is open seven days per week and, in addition to family medical care, offers Dental, Walk-In Care, Pharmacy, Physical Therapy, Podiatry, and X-ray.";s:10:"post_title";s:56:"Christopher Johnston, DO, Joins Helen Hunt Health Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:54:"christopher-johnston-do-joins-helen-hunt-health-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 13:49:50";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 17:49:50";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=522";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"525";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-18 13:51:45";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-18 17:51:45";s:12:"post_content";s:1497:"PCHC is pleased to announce that Cynthia Levick, FNP-C, has joined the medical staff of PCHC’s Helen Hunt Health Center, 242 Brunswick Street, Old Town to provide Walk-In Care Services. Ms. Levick’s practice centers on all aspects of high-quality acute medical care and treatment.

Cynthia Levick, FNP-C, received an undergraduate degree from Cornell University and a Master’s Degree in Public Health from Tulane University, followed by a Master’s of Science in Nursing from Johns Hopkins University School of Nursing and a Post Masters Psychiatric Mental Health Nurse Practitioner Certificate Program at Husson University. Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Ms. Levick served as a Family Nurse Practitioner for Sebasticook Family Doctors. Robert Allen, MD, PCHC’s Executive Medical Director, states, “PCHC is pleased to announce the addition of Cynthia Levick to its staff at the Walk-In Clinic at the Helen Hunt Health Center (HHHC) in Old Town. Ms. Levick is an excellent, experienced provider who will do an excellent job for the patients in Old Town who come to HHHC for Walk-In Care.”

Ms. Levick is a member of the Maine Nurse Practitioners Association and is seeing patients at Helen Hunt Health Center’s Walk-In Care which is open to the public and does not require an appointment. Helen Hunt Health Center is open seven days per week and, in addition to Walk-In Care, offers Family Medical Care, Pharmacy, Dental, Physical Therapy, Podiatry, and X-ray.";s:10:"post_title";s:53:"Cynthia Levick, FNP-C, Joins Helen Hunt Health Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:51:"cynthia-levick-fnp-c-joins-helen-hunt-health-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 13:53:15";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 17:53:15";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=525";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:5;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"528";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-16 13:53:44";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-16 17:53:44";s:12:"post_content";s:1765:"<p align="left">Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) has been recognized as a "Leader in LGBT Healthcare Equality" in the Healthcare Equality Index 2013, an annual survey conducted by the Human Rights Campaign (HRC) Foundation, the educational arm of the country’s largest lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender (LGBT) organization. PCHC earned top marks for its commitment to equitable, inclusive care for LGBT patients and their families, who can face significant challenges in securing adequate healthcare.</p>
Kenneth Schmidt, MPA, President and CEO states, "PCHC has long been committed to ensuring access for everyone to high quality health care services. With about 70,000 patients in the greater Bangor area, we are proud of the nationally recognized person-centered care we provide to all of our patients, including those in the LGBT community."

PCHC was one of a select group of 464 healthcare facilities nationwide to be named Leaders in LGBT Healthcare Equality. Facilities awarded this title meet key criteria for equitable care, including non-discrimination policies for LGBT patients and employees, a guarantee of equal visitation for same-sex partners and parents, and LGBT health education for key staff members.

PCHC was congratulated by HRC Health &amp; Aging Director Shane Snowdon. "LGBT patients deeply appreciate the welcoming environment provided by a Leader in LGBT Healthcare Equality. It makes a big difference to know that your local healthcare facility is fully committed to giving you the same care it gives your neighbors and co-workers."

For more information about the Healthcare Equality Index 2013, or to download a free copy of the report, visit <a href="http://www.hrc.org/hei" target="_blank">www.hrc.org/hei</a>.";s:10:"post_title";s:45:"PCHC Named Leader in LGBT Healthcare Equality";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:45:"pchc-named-leader-in-lgbt-healthcare-equality";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 13:55:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 17:55:05";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=528";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:6;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"531";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-11 13:56:50";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-11 17:56:50";s:12:"post_content";s:1609:"Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is pleased to announce that Luminita Schiop, DDS, Pediatric Dentist, has joined the staff of PCHC’s Dental Center at 1048 Union Street, Bangor.  Dr. Schiop will provide high-quality oral health care services for children.

Luminita Schiop, DDS, an undergraduate of Barnard College, Columbia University, received her Doctor of Dental Surgery degree from the New York University College of Dentistry.  Dr. Schiop completed a General Practice Residency at St. Charles Hospital and Rehabilitation Center in Port Jefferson, NY, and a Pediatric Dentistry Residency at North Bronx Healthcare Network, Bronx, NY. Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Dr. Schiop provided Pediatric Dentistry in private practice.  Robert Allen, MD, MHCM, FACC, Executive Medical Director, states, “PCHC is very pleased to have Dr. Schiop join its Pediatric Dental Staff.  Dr. Schiop brings a wealth of experience and expertise to the program and patients will find her to be very caring and competent.”

Dr. Schiop is certified by the American Board of Pediatric Dentistry and has active memberships in the College of Diplomates of the ABPD, AAPD, ADA, NYSDA, QCDS.  Dr. Schiop is accepting new pediatric dental patients. For an appointment please call 207-945-5247.  PCHC has the largest public or private dental practice north of Boston, as well as Maine’s only Accredited General Practice Dental Residency and only Accredited Pediatric Dental Residency.  In all, PCHC employs 24 fully licensed dentists, as well as about 15 registered dental hygienists.";s:10:"post_title";s:50:"Luminita Schiop, DDS, Joins PCHC’s Dental Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:45:"luminita-schiop-dds-joins-pchcs-dental-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 13:58:31";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 17:58:31";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=531";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:7;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"534";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-09 13:59:10";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-09 17:59:10";s:12:"post_content";s:1330:"Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is pleased to announce that Laura Connors, PA-C, has joined the medical staff of PCHC’s Community Care and Geriatrics whose multi provider team serves patients in area nursing homes, rehabilitation facilities, or for in-home visits. Ms. Connors’ practice centers on all aspects of high-quality geriatric medical care, including patient physicals, acute visits, and health care maintenance.

Ms. Connors received her undergraduate degree from Rivier University and her Master of Physician Assistant Studies (MPAS) from Massachusetts College of Pharmacy and Health Science. Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Ms. Connors received extensive clinical training at hospitals in Maine and New Hampshire, as well as additional experience in orthopedics. Robert Allen, MD, PCHC’s Executive Medical Director, states, “PCHC is very pleased to have Laura Connors, PA-C, on its staff. Laura is bright, energetic, and caring and will be a great help for the patients of Community Care and Geriatrics and their families.”

Ms. Connors is a member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants and will be seeing patients at area nursing and rehabilitation facilities. For more information on PCHC’s Community Care &amp; Geriatrics, please call 207-945-5247, extension 1598.";s:10:"post_title";s:63:"Laura Connors, PA-C, Joins PCHC’s Community Care & Geriatrics";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:56:"laura-connors-pa-c-joins-pchcs-community-care-geriatrics";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 14:00:42";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 18:00:42";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=534";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:8;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"537";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-06-27 14:02:05";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-27 18:02:05";s:12:"post_content";s:1232:"Leah Barteaux, Labor Ready Branch Manager, presented Ann Giggey, Hope House Manager, and Hope House staff with a check for $500 from Labor Ready’s National Headquarters on Wednesday, June 12<sup>th</sup>.  The Hope House was nominated for the funding by the local Labor Ready who hoped to recognize the efforts of the shelter and for consistently providing the company with workers.

Ann Giggey, Hope House Manager, states, “We are grateful for the recognition and support of Labor Ready and are pleased to collaborate with them to help employ Hope House guests.”

Hope House is a 64 bed emergency homeless shelter licensed by MSHA and the Office of Substance Abuse, the 2nd largest shelter in the state of Maine.  Hope House provides an integrated medical model of care for homeless guests consisting medical care, psychiatric care, and case management services.  In addition to housing and health care services, three meals per day are provided with assistance from various community groups.  Hope House is the community safety net in Bangor, managing the city of Bangor’s overflow of homeless persons from other shelters.  Hope House is running over capacity serving more than 80 homeless persons per night.";s:10:"post_title";s:42:"Hope House Receives Check from Labor Ready";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:42:"hope-house-receives-check-from-labor-ready";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 14:03:36";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 18:03:36";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=537";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:9;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"540";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-06-25 14:04:03";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-25 18:04:03";s:12:"post_content";s:1329:"Jonas Westbrook, Doctor of Dental Surgery (DDS), has joined the dental center staff at PCHC’s Helen Hunt Health Center, 242 Brunswick Street, Old Town to provide high-quality oral health care for all ages.

Dr. Westbrook received his undergraduate degree from Boston College, his Doctor of Dental Surgery Degree from State University of New York at Buffalo School of Dental Medicine, and complete Advanced Education in General Dentistry at the University of North Carolina School of Dentistry.  Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Dr. Westbrook served as Dental Director for Health Access Network in Lincoln.  Robert Allen, MD, PCHC’s Executive Medical Director, states, “PCHC is very pleased to have Dr.  Westbrook staff the Dental Practice at the Helen Hunt Health Center in Old Town.  Dr. Westbrook is an extremely caring and competent dentist who will offer the people of Old Town excellent dental care.”

Dr. Westbrook, a member of the American Dental Association as well as the Maine Dental Association, is accepting new dental patients at Helen Hunt Health Center; for an appointment please call 207-827-6128.  Helen Hunt Health Center is open seven days per week and in addition to dental care offers family medical care, Walk-In Care, Pharmacy, Physical Therapy, Podiatry, and X-ray.";s:10:"post_title";s:52:"Jonas Westbrook, DDS, Joins Helen Hunt Dental Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:50:"jonas-westbrook-dds-joins-helen-hunt-dental-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-20 14:05:20";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-20 18:05:20";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=540";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:10;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"543";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-06-20 14:10:49";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-20 18:10:49";s:12:"post_content";s:999:"Jacques Weinstein, MBA, Certified General Appraiser, Appraisal Connection, LLC, has joined PCHC's Board of Directors.  Jennifer Eastman, Esq., PCHC Board Chair, states, “Jacques is well-known within the community with over 28 years of experience in the appraisal business.  We are pleased to welcome him to our Board of Directors where his contributions will support our mission and values.”

Mr. Weinstein has been employed with Appraisal Connection, LLC, since 2005.  Mr. Weinstein received his undergraduate degree from New York University and his Masters of Business Administration from State University of New York.  Mr. Weinstein currently serves as President of the Maine Appraisers Forum.

